{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"subscript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"safe"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"index"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sl5IndexQa","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Index"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Element"},{"kind":"text","text":"? { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"index","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The position of the element to access.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the index is within the bounds of the collection, ","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"the element at that position is returned. Otherwise, ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Return Value","type":"heading","anchor":"return-value","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The element at the specified index if it is within the collection’s bounds; otherwise, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This subscript provides a safe way to access elements within the collection by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"returning ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instead of crashing when accessing an index out of bounds.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is useful for avoiding runtime errors when the exact count of the collection","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"might not be known or when dealing with dynamic data sources.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This approach ensures that attempts to access indices outside the valid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"range simply result in ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", allowing for more graceful handling of such cases.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Example usage:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]","if let number = numbers[safe: 3] {","    print(number) \/\/ Prints \"4\"","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\")","}","","if let outOfBoundsNumber = numbers[safe: 10] {","    print(outOfBoundsNumber)","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\") \/\/ Prints \"Index out of bounds\"","}"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This method enhances the safety and readability of collection access, ","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"especially in more complex logic where bounds checks are necessary.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/collection\/subscript(safe:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"Swift","modules":[{"relatedModules":["Swift"],"name":"SwiftExtras"}],"conformance":{"constraints":[{"code":"Self","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"Collection","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"availabilityPrefix":[{"text":"Available when","type":"text"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"text":"Conforms when","type":"text"}]},"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"subscript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"safe"},{"kind":"text","text":" _: "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s: